- [ ] Explain what a token is used for.

A token is like a key or password.
It only allows access to a database if you have the correct token.

- [ ] What steps can you take in your web apps to keep your data secure?

You can create a log in page that retrieves a token.
You can then create a Private Route that only gives access if the token is correct.

- [ ] Describe how web servers work.

Web servers dispense the web pages that are requested.
Requests are sent out and data is sent back.
Web servers handle these requests.

- [ ] Which HTTP methods can be mapped to the CRUD acronym that we use when interfacing with APIs/Servers.
 Create: post
 Read: get
 Update: put
 Delete: delete